column5: Andofizwe
Bill
My buddy just purchased a camp on O'Sullivan, they plan on renovated the main camp as well as a couple outpost camps. I'm heading there for a work week the end of may, looking forward to it.
Is it the Old O’Sulivan Lake Outfitters they bought from Howard?If so I tried their new website but it does not work so if you have it send it to me…thanks
Check your pm's
The old website comes up but on the front page it says come meet the new owners just click on it,it's a long name it starts with A.Just type in O'Sullivan lake outfitters

We have stayed at both 7 Lakes and Lower Twin camps. If the water is low the docks are shallow at Lower Twin but manageable. Better docking and more protected at 7 Lakes. More a numbers spot than size but have caught up to 28 inchers

Only know about the twin lakes as a starting point for fly-ins, have never heard about how good it is until the above posts. I am, however, very familiar with O'Sullivan Lake. Stayed a number of times at O'Sullivan's Rainbow( the other camp, this one is actually right on the lake, rather than being up the river a bit, which flows in to O'S). Fishing around that camp and further to the right, out of camp can be very good for walleyes, not so much the other way - which has been my last experience, others may have had other results. Owners of O'Sullivan's Rainbow are great folks who try very hard to be helpful. Fish the wind! Bill
